Sports Direct International Plc (SPD) 
founder Mike Ashley is close to buying an 80 percent stake in
two fashion retail chains owned by U.K. entrepreneur Tom Hunter,
USC and Cruise, for 7 million pounds ($11 million), the
Financial Times reported, citing people familiar with the deal.  Sports Direct will invest about 20 million pounds to
develop the businesses and open new stores, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
